1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4 3. h4 {Besides c5 and d5, black can play some other moves
like: h6, c6, Nxg5 or g6} h6 {Logical move. Black wants to play e6} (3... Nxg5
{Premature! Black revealed his attentions} 4. hxg5 d5 5. e3 g6 6. f4 Bg7 7. Nf3
c5 8. c3 Nc6 9. Nbd2 {You probably remember this position.. You noticed that
many position coincide. It's the same position like before, just, move order
is different}) (3... g6 4. Nd2 Nxg5 (4... Nxd2 {Not so good move for black..
He activates our queen} 5. Qxd2 Bg7 6. Bh6 $1 O-O (6... Bxh6 7. Qxh6 d5 8. Qg7
Rf8 9. Nf3 Qd6 10. O-O-O Nd7 11. Ng5 Nf6 12. e3 Bd7 13. h5 $16 {And white is
much better..}) 7. h5 $18 {It's winning position for white..}) (4... d5 5. Nxe4
dxe4 6. e3 Bg7 7. c3 h6 8. Bf4 O-O 9. Qc2 Bf5 10. Ne2 Nc6 11. Ng3 $14) 5. hxg5
Bg7 6. e3 d5 7. f4 {Again the same..}) (3... c6 {Black aims to activate his
queen to b6 or a5} 4. Nd2 Nxd2 (4... d5 {Black can leave his Knight on e4. In
that case, we are going to take there} 5. Nxe4 dxe4 6. c3 {Good move. We want
to eliminate Qa5+} Bf5 7. e3 h6 8. Bf4 Nd7 9. g4 $14 {Almost the same position
like before..}) 5. Qxd2 d5 6. e3 {Again, black need to play h6 and we will
have almost the same position like before...}) 4. Bf4 {Because of h6, it's
quite difficult for black to play 0-0, because, whte can play g4-g5 with quick
attack} d5 (4... c5 {We can do the same thing like before..} 5. dxc5 Qa5+ 6.
Nd2 Nxd2 7. Qxd2 Qxc5 8. e4 d6 {It's a good opportunity for white to put the
knight on c3! In that sense, Ne2 is the best move} 9. Ne2 Nc6 10. Nc3 Bd7 11.
O-O-O g6 12. Nd5 Rc8 13. Be3 Qa5 14. Qxa5 Nxa5 15. Bxa7 $16 {This is one
example how you should play this position}) 5. Nd2 Bf5 6. Nxe4 Bxe4 7. f3 Bh7
8. e3 {It's the same position like before...} *

